headline: JPM says buy these 2 auto supplier stocks over Tesla
summary: Investing.com -- JPMorgan analysts said in a note Tuesday that they recommend investors sell Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) and instead buy auto parts suppliers Aptiv (NYSE:APTV) and BorgWarner (NYSE:BWA), arguing that supplier shares offer "relative value."

headline: Harbor Disciplined Bond ETF Q1 2025 Commentary
